parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ignition switch shorts
causing a fire; smoke comes out of the tilt steering column; the vehicle catches on fire while parked or driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The alternator catches on fire; a plug connector to the alternator melts down
causing the car to shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls; the engine cranks but does not start; the vehicle stalls in an intersection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke starts coming out of the tilt steering column; the vehicle catches on fire while parked or driving; the headlight switch overheats and burns insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Side Seat Belt Latch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat belt latch can lead to the seat belt becoming unbuckled while driving, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's side seat belt will not latch
the driver's side seat belt unlatches while driving
the driver's side seat belt does not stay latched.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retraction mechanism can cause the seat belt to not tighten properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front driver and passenger side seat belts do not retract back and tighten up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shoulder belt can cause the driver to not be properly restrained during an accident, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The shoulder belt part of the seat failed to hold the driver in place during an accident
causing injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil pan corrosion and leaks can cause engine damage, lead to engine failure, and potentially result in a vehicle fire, which can pose a significant risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: Oil leaks
oil drips or puddles under the vehicle
rust or corrosion on the oil pan
engine noise or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and hard starting can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle stalls while in motion, and can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
engine hesitation
rough idling
loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause serious injury or death, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: Flames or smoke coming from the vehicle
burning smell
engine overheating.
